thrived as a capital of the first

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Ethiopian Kingdom founded at the end of

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
the first century

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:19.000
Aksum is also a Christian holy site the

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.000
Ethiopian Orthodox Church continues to

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
follow early Christian teachings

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:32.000
practices and traditions these 20 metre

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
high stone monuments standing in the

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
centre of the town are the tombstones of

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.000
ancient kings people here practiced an

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.000
ancient religion before Christianity was

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
introduced this Halfmoon shape

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:53.000
represents the god of the moon

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Christianity was introduced to a tomb

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
during the 4th century the Church of st.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.000
Mary of Zion was built at around that

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:07.000
time the legend on how action became a

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:11.000
sacred site is depicted here during the

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:13.000
9th century the Queen of Sheba who

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.000
dominated this region fell in love with

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:19.000
King Solomon of Israel and had a son

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.000
named Menelik the first Menelik the

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:24.000
first became the first king of Ethiopia

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.000
he acquired the Ark containing the

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.000
tablets of the Ten Commandments and

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.000
brought it to Aksum the Ark of the

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Covenant was then brought to this church

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.000
the entrance to the sacred room where

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:39.000
the Ark is kept is protected by two

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:48.000
angels holding swords

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:51.000
the sacred Ark can only be seen by the

00:01:51.000 --> 00:02:01.000
public on the day of a festival

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:04.000
however no one has ever actually seen

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.000
what is inside as it is prohibited to

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.000
open the Ark this festival is carried

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.000
out to celebrate the day when Jesus

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.000
Christ was baptized the climax of the

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:19.000
festival is a large-scale baptism

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:22.000
ceremony attended by the local

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:31.000
Christians

